<center><h2>Warm ups</h2></center>
<br>
<div class="row">
  <div class="column">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="container">
        <img src="../../../images/line.PNG" alt="Jane" style="width:100%">
      <div class="container">
        <h4>General Warm up</h4>
        <p class="title">10-20 minutes</p>
       <p><b>Set Up</b>: 4 cones in 2 lines</p>
        <p><b>Players Needed:</b> size of your squad</p>
        <p><b>Explanation:</b> A simple way of performing a dynamic warm-up is to have players go through different locomotions together in linesThere are plenty of great locomotions that coaches can use in dynamic warm-ups such as jogging lunges, squats, skippiing, high knees, butt kicks and many more</p>
        <center><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=orZKw7CrGdY" target="_blank"><p><button style="width:250px" class="button">Video <i class="fab fa-youtube"></i></button></p></a></center>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

  <div class="column">
    <div class="card">
        <img src="../../../images/realy.PNG" alt="Jane" style="width:100%">
      <div class="container">
        <h4>Relay Warm-ups</h4>
        <p class="title">2-10 minutes</p>
       <p><b>Set Up</b>: 4 cones in 2 lines</p>
        <p><b>Players Needed:</b> the size of your squad</p>
        <p><b>Explanation:</b>Once players have finished going through some dynamic locomotions, relay races can be used to prepare players even further. Players enjoy the competitive aspect of relays. In addition, relay races are great for players to work on speed, agility, and quickness.As players will often times go through a dynamic warm-up in lines, it can be very easy to transition into a relay race in lines.</p>
       <center><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aHpyERP58N8" target="_blank"><p><button style="width:250px" class="button">Video <i class="fab fa-youtube"></i></button></p></a></center>
       <br>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

<div class="column">
    <div class="card">
      <img src="../../../images/pass.png" alt="Mike" style="width:100%">
      <div class="container">
        <h4>Passing line warm-up</h4>
        <p class="title">5-10 minutes</p>
       <p><b>Set Up</b>:cones 10 yards apart.</p>
        <p><b>Players Needed:</b> your squad</p>
        <p><b>Explanation:</b> Players just play the ball to the man directly in font of them and runs to the back of that line after the pass.Make players only use thier right foot and then their left foot. Limit their touches to one or two touches</p>
        <center><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y91WBDukbhg&t=76s" target="_blank"><p><button style="width:250px" class="button">Video <i class="fab fa-youtube"></i></button></p></a></center>
